NBA FINALS: SPURS v HEAT
June 16, 2013
Erik Spoelstra
START_OF_INTERVIEW_TEXT
 
 
  
 
  
  
   
 Q.   Erik, this morning when I asked Chris what he's going to do between the morning and the game, he said, "be a mess."   Just how tough is it this time of year for everybody just to kind of get their composure and their poise to just deal with all the pressure?   
COACH ERIK SPOELSTRA:   This is the life we chose.   You know, you feel alive at this time of year, even coming off a win or a loss.   The toughest part is waiting two days to play the next game.   But we're finally here, so let's tip this thing up.   
   
  
  
  
  
  

END_OF_INTERVIEW_TEXT